{
  "doc_id": "45519",
  "text": "By using such contrastive experimental designs, two candidate electrophysiological NCCs have emerged: visual awareness negativity (VAN) and late positivity (LP). VAN is the negative amplitude difference between aware and unaware conditions [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . It typically appears around 200 ms (N1-N2 latency range or N200) in posterior temporal and occipital electrodes [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . LP is the positive amplitude difference between aware and unaware condition in the P3 time window [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . LP is typically found at parietal electrodes [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] .",
